  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Time of Elimination of Phenytoin in Patients With Elevated Phenytoin Levels</measure>
    <time_frame>Serum phenytoin levels were obtained every 6 hours for 24 hours then once every 24 hours</time_frame>
    <description>We enrolled patients with elevated phenytoin levels into the study with greater than 30 ug/cc. The treatment arm received multiple doses of activated charcoal and the control arm received no activated charcoal. We obtained serum phenytoin levels every 6 hours for 24 hours then once every 24 hours. The time to reach a subtoxic level was determined in each arm by looking at serum phenytoin levels and documenting when it was below 25 ug/cc.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
